  "text": "The shorter TTP contractions might be seen as an improvement of the generalized motor program in participants. Generalized motor programs are abstract motor memory composed of fixed and flexible information for executing movements. In faster movements, the movement time decreases and the TTP contractions decreases with movement time. According to Carter and Sharprio [CITATION_1] , this feature is inherent in the structure of generalized motor programs.",
